    <h1>Story objects</h1>
    <p class="lede">Story objects are concrete things that gain meaning through use, scene, place, and relationship.</p>
    <p>A bridge, tool, token, carved mark, cloth, vessel, or small held thing can keep emotional weight long after a scene has passed.</p>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">First object thread</p>
      <h2>The bridge</h2>
      <p>The bridge is the first clear story object because Lina’s path begins with a crossing. It becomes a test of listening, courage, care, and attention.</p>
      <p>In Lina’s first story, the bridge is active in the scene. It asks whether someone can hear what others miss, respond carefully, and cross without turning wonder into noise.</p>
